http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/College-Bazaar-begins-at-Kongu-College/article14008837.ece

Women self-help groups from several districts have showcased their products for sale at the Kongu Arts and Science College.The College Bazaar, a three-day activity, was initiated on Tuesday by the institution’s Women Development Cell in association with Mahalir Thittam, under the aegis of Tamil Nadu State Rural Livelihood Mission.The transactions were formally inaugurated by the Correspondent of Kongu Polytechnic College C. Kumarasamy, in the presence of the KASC Principal N. Raman, and Project Director of Mahalir Thittam Palanikumar.The College had already hosted College Bazaar twice in recent years.This time around, there were 50 SHGs selling self-manufactured jute bags, leather bags, toys, and food products made of grain raised through nature farming.Students feel encouraged to take to entrepreneurship on learning about the bold initiatives of the women many of whom lack formal education, P. Poongudi, Director of the College’s Women Development Cell and Head, Department of Management, said.Students are being given one hour slots to visit the stalls and patronise the SHGs.Members of women SHGs from several districts have showcased their products